$interpreted: Jihasaha: ...Seeing you frown after reading that letter... could it be that—
Tindoiimu: It's the same as before. Everything is fine at home, and the queen hopes I can focus on my duties...
Jihasaha: I see...
Tindoiimu: These letters are all the same. Something isn't right... Clearly what happened at the Metamorphosis was a huge deal...
Tindoiimu: Jihasaha, is everything really going as smoothly as the letters make it seem?
Jihasaha: .........
Tindoiimu: Jihasaha, do not make me lose your trust as well!
Jihasaha: ...I dare not conceal anything from the princess...
Jihasaha: They're only rumors. The king and queen probably just didn't want to worry you.
Tindoiimu: Rumors?
Jihasaha: ...Very well. If you must know...
Jihasaha: After what happened, some complained that you lacked discipline. Others berated the royal family for bowing to the East Alliance.
Jihasaha: However, both sides—
Tindoiimu: Are not satisfied with me serving as a political hostage...
Jihasaha: That is why I said you didn't need to worry.

Jihasaha: The pressure that the East Alliance has put on everybody—people need someone to blame and have made you the scapegoat. 
You must be more aware of this than anyone.
Tindoiimu: ...I understand, but...
Tindoiimu: But...
Tindoiimu: ...Tingko?
Tingko: S-So heavy... and, I can't... see in front of me...
Tingko: Waa... aah!!
Jihasaha: Are you okay?
Tingko: Jihasaha!?
Tingko: And the princess! You're back!
Jihasaha: .........
Jihasaha: Energetic as always. I'm happy to see that.
Tingko: So nice to see you, too, Jihasaha~
Tingko: Have you come with another letter?
Jihasaha: Yes.
Jihasaha: And what is all this?
Tingko: Gifts from the qilin lord. He's trying to buy her favor.
Tingko: But they don't fit inside the house. After the lord left, I wanted to organize everything, but...
Tindoiimu: He left? Has he given up?
Tingko: Nope, he was actually super smiley. Said that since you weren't here, he'd return at nightfall.
Tindoiimu: He's coming back? Ugh...
Jihasaha: Is the qilin lord bothering the princess?
Tingko: Yeah, and he won't give up no matter how much the princess refuses.
Tindoiimu: I need to learn from my mistakes... I can't keep doing things that invite criticism.
Tindoiimu: I've got to think of some way to get out of this...
Jihasaha: Leave it up to me. I'll deal with this once and for all.
Tindoiimu: ...No. He may be a pest, but he is the esteemed lord of the Qilin Tribe.
Jihasaha: And? I'll take care of it without anyone finding out.
Tindoiimu: It's not just that. He is virtuous. His intentions align with his actions.
Tindoiimu: ...Compared to others in the East Alliance I've met these past nine years, he's truly worthy of being called a good person...
Tindoiimu: I cannot harm a good person for my own well-being.
Tingko: Princess...
Jihasaha: ...Since that's how you feel.
Tindoiimu: You don't disagree?
Jihasaha: Words like these are what caused me to follow you in the first place. How could I disagree?
Tingko: But if Lord Juan Yun never gives up...
Tindoiimu: Then maybe...
Tindoiimu: Jihasaha, Tingko, I think I've got a plan!
Jihasaha: It sounds dangerous... but I will obey the princess.
Tingko: I'll go see who I can find!
Tindoiimu: Thank you both.
